{"id":2143,"date":"2019-09-01T21:41:59","date_gmt":"2019-09-01T19:41:59","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.klubpolarny.pl\/?p=2143"},"modified":"2019-09-02T10:22:16","modified_gmt":"2019-09-02T08:22:16","slug":"poszukiwane-informacje-o-chacie-na-palffyodden","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.klubpolarny.pl\/aktualnosci\/wiesci\/poszukiwane-informacje-o-chacie-na-palffyodden\/","title":{"rendered":"Poszukiwane informacje o chacie na Palffyodden"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span lang=\"pl-PL\">Na p\u00f3\u0142nocno-zachodnim skraju S\u00f8rkapplandu, czyli najbardziej na po\u0142udnie wysuni\u0119tego skrawka wyspy Spitsbergen, w miejscu, w kt\u00f3rym nied\u017awiedzie polarne s\u0105 cz\u0119stszymi go\u015b\u0107mi ni\u017c ludzie, stoi chata. Jest to stara chata traperska, kt\u00f3r\u0105 w 1966 roku zbudowa\u0142o dw\u00f3ch m\u0142odych Norweg\u00f3w \u2013 Terje Ovlien ze Skotterud i Einar Sletbakk z Narviku. Nazwali j\u0105 <\/span><span lang=\"pl-PL\"><b>Kapp Horn<\/b><\/span><span lang=\"pl-PL\">, a przyl\u0105dek, na kt\u00f3rym si\u0119 znajduje znany jest jako <\/span><span lang=\"pl-PL\"><b>Palffyodden<\/b><\/span><span lang=\"pl-PL\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span lang=\"pl-PL\">W roku 1973, S\u00f8rkappland sta\u0142 si\u0119 cz\u0119\u015bci\u0105 parku narodowego S\u00f8r- Spitsbergen, w rezultacie czego chata Kapp Horn nie mog\u0142a ju\u017c pe\u0142ni\u0107 swojej pierwotnej funkcji. Wkr\u00f3tce potem, s\u0142uch po jej w\u0142a\u015bcicielach zagin\u0105\u0142.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span lang=\"pl-PL\">Chata Kapp Horn lata \u015bwietno\u015bci ma ju\u017c za sob\u0105, ale wci\u0105\u017c dzielnie opiera si\u0119 staro\u015bci i bezlitosnej arktycznej pogodzie, s\u0142u\u017c\u0105c jako schronienie dla podr\u00f3\u017cnik\u00f3w i naukowc\u00f3w, kt\u00f3rzy od czasu do czasu pojawiaj\u0105 si\u0119 w okolicy. \u015awiadcz\u0105 o tym wpisy w ksi\u0105\u017cce go\u015bci, z kt\u00f3rych najstarszy pochodzi z 1987 roku! Co dzia\u0142o si\u0119 z chat\u0105 do tego czasu? Jak si\u0119 zmienia\u0142a? Czego szukali w niej ci, kt\u00f3rzy pozostawili po sobie jedynie podzi\u0119kowanie i podpis? Tego nie wiemy, ale liczymy na to, \u017ce \u2013 z Wasz\u0105 pomoc\u0105 \u2013 uda nam si\u0119 dotrze\u0107 do ludzi, kt\u00f3rzy wiedz\u0105 i b\u0119d\u0105 ch\u0119tni rzuci\u0107 troch\u0119 \u015bwiat\u0142a na histori\u0119 chaty Kapp Horn, kt\u00f3ra latem tego roku sta\u0142a si\u0119 sezonow\u0105 baz\u0105 Fundacji forScience, a tym samym odegra\u0142a drobn\u0105, acz zaszczytn\u0105 rol\u0119 w obchodach 100-lecia polsko norweskich stosunk\u00f3w mi\u0119dzynarodowych!<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span lang=\"pl-PL\">Je\u015bli macie jakiekolwiek zdj\u0119cia, informacje lub wspomnienia dotycz\u0105ce chaty na Palffyodden albo kt\u00f3rego\u015b z jej budowniczych, piszcie do nas koniecznie na adres <a href=\"mailto:biuro@forScience.pl\">biuro@forScience.pl<\/a>.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span lang=\"pl-PL\">Serdecznie dzi\u0119kujemy za pomoc,<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span lang=\"pl-PL\">Basia i Adam z Fundacji forScience<\/span><\/p>\n<p><a name=\"_GoBack\"><\/a><span lang=\"pl-PL\">Wi\u0119cej informacji o chacie Kapp Horn i o tym, co tam robimy, znajdziecie na <a href=\"http:\/\/www.facebook.com\/FundacjaforScience\/\">www.facebook.com\/FundacjaforScience\/<\/a> i na <a href=\"http:\/\/www.forScience.pl\">www.forScience.pl<\/a>.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span class=\"_5mfr\"><span class=\"_6qdm\">??<\/span><\/span> If you\u2019re into detective mysteries set against the magnificent backdrop of the Arctic, you\u2019re in for a treat!<\/p>\n<p>On the north-western edge of S\u00f8rkappland, which forms the southernmost tip of Spitsbergen, in an area visited more often by polar bears than people, stands a cabin. It\u2019s an old trapper\u2019s cabin, built in 1966 by two young Norwegians \u2013 Terje Ovlien from Skotterud and Einar Sletbakk from Narvik. They called it Kapp Horn, and the piece of land where it\u2019s located is known as Palffyodden.<\/p>\n<p>In 1973, S\u00f8rkappland became part of the newly-established S\u00f8r-Spitsbergen National Park, as a result of which the cabin could no longer serve its original function. It was soon afterwards that Terje Ovlien and Einar Sletbakk were heard of for the last time. The fact remains, however, that \u2013 as far as we know \u2013 the cabin is still officially their private property.<\/p>\n<p>Although Kapp Horn Hytte is quite clearly past its prime, it\u2019s still bravely resisting old age and harsh weather conditions, offering shelter to travellers and scientists, who occasionally venture into the area. Brief glimpses into the cabin\u2019s history can be found in the messages left in the visitor\u2019s book, the oldest of which comes from 1987. What was going on with the cabin until that time? How has it changed? What happened to its owners? Who were the people whose messages were limited to a thank you and a signature? And what did they do and see in Palffyodden? This we don\u2019t know, but we believe that \u2013 with your help \u2013 we\u2019ll manage to reach those who do. In fact, we hope that, at some point, our message will also reach Terje Ovlien and Einar Sletbakk, because we\u2019re dying to ask them about the early days of Kapp Horn Hytte, which half a century later became a seasonal base for forScience Foundation and thus played a part in the celebrations marking the centenary of diplomatic relations between Poland and Norway!<\/p>\n<p>If you happen to have any photographs, factual information or private memories related to the cabin in Palffyodden or either of its owners, do contact us on Facebook or at biuro@forScience.pl. If you don\u2019t, help us find those who do by sharing this post with your friends.<\/p>\n<p>Many thanks!<br \/>\nBasia and Adam from forScience Foundation<\/p>\n<p>For more information on Kapp Horn Hytte and what we\u2019re doing there, visit our Facebook profile or <a href=\"http:\/\/www.forScience.pl\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-ft=\"{&quot;tn&quot;:&quot;-U&quot;}\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" data-lynx-uri=\"https:\/\/l.facebook.com\/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.forScience.pl%2F&amp;h=AT0uCfXVxbVKHcPxKq7zdkDi5mepRA0lzvtLZ43zXTGntVvC0vBr3Vl3lmVz5C5VD00PynJFc3qPZWrXrNWvIRgYOD251sLI18U8cbFIxfRRnVr9Jq3R-eWS7L9eJs8WJhaihQHchOxBcAePgKslLRY9kPv5YHCNj8hvwr63ZFxkDMCGu5SLwiDBLH4q3RneDB89ptDO7tOzBrKjReiXb2HMgq7AIMqUxg8tw-80NS8ArJ70u9hFLh3BVIKInsk-_8tvGFmb0LPKF5D_zgZKR60nhQ7MveNBYKEa3pVYAct_oh3e220Xo_wKkoC6ot3x98TvjFe-Wxqw0S-Z9DmACEeKF8uYlB9onawlM6Vco8g6NyEfsd3xYs2gNniDxrRfAJRCryQZ5zjpLV9oPOCLDZjZvPeup97T1EO8l0ywKRxewMATlHqyI56Evdsr45DOAe8f93OoBk0Ha0H231rMoR3nZZ-YKaYXmGVqPx4brZqxNMrkVbLUKnkEGFikiXeoWjacEsET6IkeBGCiuAhB3MZrKNkSFghKW6SjyIU-gMk-qfI2EVfak9YxmrNv4R_TegK_x3_aEss0QUmWzZv8H0x-KU7dFwACr4DzEYpMkPjfSapr9FTvC-G5kGxhOKYNGFrt8xhXouR4ic0ig1SKCx5-tlngwwYPbqpd\">www.forScience.pl.<\/a><\/p>\n<p>P.S. If you decide to post a comment directly below this content, PLEASE REMEMBER TO TAG US! Otherwise, due to individual privacy settings, we may have no access to what you have written.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span class=\"_5mfr\"><span class=\"_6qdm\">??<\/span><\/span> Hvis dere er glad i g\u00e5ter og detektivhistorier som skjer midt i det magiske, arktiske landskapet, vi har noe til dere!<\/p>\n<p>P\u00e5 nordvestlige kanten av S\u00f8rkapp Land, det vil si p\u00e5 den s\u00f8rligste delen av Spitsbergen, der du mye oftere f\u00e5r bes\u00f8k av en isbj\u00f8rn enn av et menneske, st\u00e5r ei hytte. Dette er ei gammel jegerhytte, som i 1966 ble bygget av to unge nordmenn: Terje Ovlien fra Skotterud og Einar Sletbakk fra Narvik. De kalte hytta Kapp Horn, og landstykket hytta st\u00e5r p\u00e5, er kjent som Palffyodden.<\/p>\n<p>I 1973 ble S\u00f8rkapp Land inkludert i S\u00f8r-Spitsbergen nasjonalpark som f\u00f8rte til at hytta ikke lenger kunne utf\u00f8re sin opprinnelige funksjon. Snart etter h\u00f8rte ingen mer om deres eiere. Men det endrer ikke det faktum at \u2013 if\u00f8lge v\u00e5re kilder \u2013 hytta fremdeles tilh\u00f8rer dem, i hvert fall offisielt.<\/p>\n<p>Kapp Horn hytta har sine beste \u00e5r allerede bak seg, men den fortsatt trosser sin alder og det n\u00e5del\u00f8se arktiske v\u00e6ret, og tjener som et tilfluktssted for reisende og forskere, som av og til dukker opp i omr\u00e5det. Alt er dokumentert i gjesteboka, der den eldste oppf\u00f8ringen er fra 1987! Hva har skjedd med hytta siden da? Hvordan har den forandret seg? Hva med dens eiere? Og hva med dem som bare har etterlatt seg en kort takk og en underskrift \u2013 hva drev de med der? Vi vet det ikke, men vi h\u00e5per, at \u2013 med deres hjelp \u2013 klarer vi \u00e5 komme i kontakt med folk som vet noe. Jo! Vi h\u00e5per ogs\u00e5 at b\u00e5de Terje Ovlien og Einar Sletbakk f\u00e5r vite at vi leter etter dem, for det ville bety mye for oss om vi kunne sp\u00f8rre dem om Kapp Horn hytta som etter femti \u00e5r er blitt en sesongstasjon for forScience Stiftelsen, og dermed spilte en liten, men likevel betydningsfull rolle under feiringen av 100-\u00e5rsdagen for polsk-norske internasjonale relasjoner!<\/p>\n<p>Har dere noen bilder, opplysninger eller minner om\/fra hytta p\u00e5 Palffyodden eller vet noe om dens eiere, skriv til oss p\u00e5 Facebook eller send en e-post til biuro@forScience.pl. Har dere lyst til \u00e5 hjelpe oss, men vet dessverre ikke noe om Kapp Horn hytta? Del dette innlegget!<\/p>\n<p>Tusen takk for hjelpen!<br \/>\nBasia og Adam fra forScience Stiftelsen<\/p>\n<p>Mer informasjon om Kapp Horn hytta og om hva vi driver med, finner dere p\u00e5 v\u00e5r Facebook-profil og p\u00e5 <a href=\"http:\/\/www.forScience.pl\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-ft=\"{&quot;tn&quot;:&quot;-U&quot;}\" data-lynx-mode=\"async\" data-lynx-uri=\"https:\/\/l.facebook.com\/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.forScience.pl%2F&amp;h=AT2lEwhpiNxh0pOl6Hq6E-kHL13jyrhsx7ISbvNtgb3WWCkmP5kKYs2EeUJ0ES7CWTE8RFYT83l